2) Create the dynamic config file

On your host, create:

./traefik/dynamic/wazuh-transport.yml

If you want the fastest “just make it work”:

http:
  serversTransports:
    wazuh-insecure:
      insecureSkipVerify: true

3) Add this label to your Wazuh Dashboard service
- "traefik.http.services.wazuh.loadbalancer.serversTransport=wazuh-insecure@file"

And keep:

- "traefik.http.services.wazuh.loadbalancer.server.scheme=https"
- "traefik.http.services.wazuh.loadbalancer.server.port=5601"

4) Restart
docker compose up -d --force-recreate traefik
docker restart wazuh.dashboard

✅ This resolves the “SSL alert bad certificate” caused by Traefik rejecting your internal CA cert.